          <h3 class="section__title">Privacy Policy</h3>
          <p>Effective Date: May 1, 2025</p>
          <p>At TrackIT, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and safeguard the data you provide when using our web-based task management system.</p>
          <p>The information we collect is used solely to deliver and improve the services we offer. This includes managing your account, enabling task creation and collaboration, sending notifications and summaries, and enhancing system functionality and security. We do not sell or rent your personal data to third parties. All collected data is used in accordance with this policy and applicable data protection laws.</p>
          <p>We collect certain types of information to provide and improve our services. This includes personal information such as your name, email address, and profile details when you register for an account. Additionally, we collect task-related data including titles, descriptions, and user activity logs generated within workspaces. Usage data, such as your device type, browser, IP address, and access times, may also be collected to help us monitor and optimize platform performance. Cookies and similar technologies are used to enhance user experience and understand how our platform is used.</p>
          <p>Your data is securely stored using encrypted databases and restricted access controls. Task data and activity logs are retained for a period of three (3) months. At the start of the fourth month, data from the first month is automatically deleted from our system. Prior to deletion, a PDF summary of the deleted data is generated and emailed to registered Admins and Managers to ensure records are preserved.</p>
          <p>TrackIT may rely on select third-party service providers for services such as email delivery and analytics. These providers are required to adhere to strict data protection and confidentiality standards, and we ensure that any shared information is handled responsibly and lawfully.</p>
          <p>As a user, you have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data. You may also request that we stop sending non-essential communications and disable cookies via your browser settings. If you wish to exercise these rights or inquire about your data, you may contact us directly at privacy@trackit.app.</p>
          <p>TrackIT is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from minors. Should we discover that such data has been inadvertently collected, we will take immediate steps to delete it.</p>
          <p>We reserve the right to update or revise this Privacy Policy as needed to reflect changes in our services or legal obligations. Any significant updates will be communicated to users through email or in-app notifications prior to implementation.</p>
          <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at privacy@trackit.app. Your trust is important to us, and we are dedicated to protecting your information with transparency and care.</p>
        </section>
